33:21.233 --> 33:23.201 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Walter. WALTER ISAACSON, Author,
"Einstein: His Life and

33:23.235 --> 33:25.203 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Universe": Good to be back,
Gwen. GWEN IFILL: You have said

33:25.237 --> 33:27.305 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that the theory, the general
theory of relativity -- I'm

33:27.339 --> 33:29.774 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
going to say that right -- is
the most beautiful theory in the

33:29.808 --> 33:33.645 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
history of science. What do you
