bowling ball. Why? Not because

36:30.221 --> 36:33.224 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the bowling ball has some
mysterious attraction at a

36:33.258 --> 36:35.794 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
distance, but because the ball
has curved the fabric of the

36:35.827 --> 36:39.497 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
trampoline. And what Einstein is
able to visualize is that a big

36:39.531 --> 36:43.968 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
mass moving curves not just the
fabric of the trampoline, but

36:44.002 --> 36:47.772 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
all four dimensions of space and
time. GWEN IFILL: You talk about

36:47.806 --> 36:51.509 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
