36:51.543 --> 36:54.946 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WALTER ISAACSON: Yes. He gets to
call them gedankenexperiment,

36:54.979 --> 36:57.315 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
which means thought experiments.
These are things where he

36:57.348 --> 37:01.119 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
imagines what happens if a big
object is rolling across a

37:01.152 --> 37:04.389 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
fabric. And it's just
imagination, what we might call

37:04.422 --> 37:08.693 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
daydreaming. He never did
physical experiments in a lab.

37:08.726 --> 37:12.831 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He just did the experiments
visualizing concepts in his head

37:12.864 --> 37:16.334 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and said, well, what if I caught
up with a light beam? Or what if

37:16.367 --> 37:20.338 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I were in the car -- an elevator
car accelerating upward in outer

37:20.371 --> 37:23.041 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
space where there is no gravity?
Or what would happen if a

37:23.074 --> 37:26.544 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
massive object rolled over a
fabric? These were the

37:26.578 --> 37:29.814 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
imaginative thought experiments
that leads him to this most

37:29.848 --> 37:33.451 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
beautiful of all theories. GWEN
IFILL: If this was never proven

37:33.485 --> 37:38.756 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
in a lab, or at least if that is
not where his ideas came from,

37:38.790 --> 37:40.758 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
has anyone ever tried in the 100
years since to debunk the

37:40.792 --> 37:42.760 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
theory? WALTER ISAACSON: Oh,
over and over again. The first

37:42.794 --> 37:46.531 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
